gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pacers 123, Rockets 117
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Tyrese Haliburton’s 33 points (7-13 3PM), six rebounds and 10 assists, the Pacers defeated the Rockets, 123-117. Myles Turner added 18 points and five rebounds for the Pacers in the victory, while Alperen Sengun tallied 30 points, 16 rebounds, five assists and four steals for the Rockets in the losing effort. Sengun has notched back-to-back games with 30+ points. The Pacers improve to 15-14 on the season, while the Rockets fall to 15-13.
